http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/Kamal-Haasan%E2%80%99s-Papanasam-is-top-rated-film/article14026721.ece

Online movie ticketing portal BookMyShow has announced ‘A Year at the Movies 2015’ that lists out the Best movies of 2015, based on user ratings and ticket sales. And Kamal Haasan’s Papanasam, the Tamil remake of Malayalam film Drishyam, features among the top three rated films by users.In a press statement, Parikshit Dar, Co-Founder & Director, BookMyShow, has been quoted as saying, “Amongst the Most Liked movies in 2015, none of the top 7 films are Hindi or English; but rather all regional features. Chhello Divas: A New Beginning (Gujarati), Papanasam (Tamil) and Katyar Kaljat Ghusali (Marathi) are top three rated movies by users.”The lists consist of the top 100 box-office hits, top 10 movies by 9 different languages, 50 most liked and 20 least liked movies that hit screens in 2015.